IRS990.MissionDesc: LEE INITIATIVES PRESERVES THE LEGACY OF LEE HOSPITAL BY MANAGING ITS RESOURCES TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR PEOPLE IN THE SERVICE AREA OF THE FORMER LEE HOSPITAL IN WEST CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA.
IRS990.Desc: TO PROVIDE GRANT FUNDS TO HEALTH RELATED ORGANIZATIONS

IRS990ScheduleA.FactsAndCircumstancesTestTxt: MISSIONOUR MISSION IS TO PRESERVE THE LEGACY OF LEE HOSPITAL BY MANAGING ITS RESOURCES TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR PEOPLE IN THE SERVICE AREA OF THE FORMER LEE HOSPITAL IN WEST CENTRAL PENNSYLVANIA. THIS IS ACCOMPLISHED BY PROVIDING GRANT FUNDS TO HEALTH RELATED ORGANIZATIONS AS WELL AS SCHOLARSHIPS TO STUDENTS FROM THE AREA THAT ARE PURSUING AN EDUCATION IN THE MEDICAL FIELD.PURPOSE1. OWN, MANAGE, AND GROW AN ENDOWMENT ACCUMULATED OVER YEARS TO BENEFIT NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS SERVING CHILDREN, YOUTH, AND FAMILIES.2. WITHIN THE LAST FIVE YEARS, LEE INITIATIVES, INC. HAS SUPPORTED NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS BY PROVIDING 225 GRANTS TOTALING OVER $4,000,000.3. WITHIN THE LAST FIVE YEARS, LEE INITIATIVES, INC. HAS SUPPORTED OVER 100 STUDENTS BY PROVIDING SCHOLARSHIPS TOTALING OVER $100,000. 4. THE ENDOWMENT WAS ACQUIRED BY FUNDS FROM LEE HOSPITAL AND IS MANAGED BY A BOARD OF DIRECTORS THAT HAVE NOT SUBSTANTIALLY CONTRIBUTED TO THE ENDOWMENT.STRUCTURELEE INITIATIVES, INC. IS A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION AND IS GOVERNED BY A BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHO ARE NOMINATED AND ELECTED TO SERVE ON THE BOARD. THESE INDIVIDUALS ARE RESPECTED MEMBERS OF THE COMMUNITY AND ARE NOT EMPLOYED BY LEE INITIATIVES, INC. MEETINGS ARE HELD REGULARLY AND BUSINESS DECISIONS ARE MADE BY MAJORITY VOTE.REVENUE SOURCESREVENUE IS RECEIVED FROM A VARIETY OF SOURCES WHICH INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING.1. ANNUAL FUNDRAISING BANQUET CONSISTING OF DONATIONS FROM INDIVIDUALS, BUSINESSES, AND CORPORATE SPONSORS.2. DONATIONS FROM COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS3. LEASE REVENUE4. MANAGEMENT FEE INCOME FOR SERVICES PROVIDED TO OTHER ORGANIZATIONS.5. INVESTMENT INCOMEPLANNING AND REGULAR ACTIVITIES TO ATTRACT DONORS AND SUPPORT INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING: PUBLIC SPEAKING ENGAGEMENTS FACILITY AND GROUNDS TOURS PRINT INFORMATIONAL MATERIALS ONE TO ONE CONTACTS SPECIAL EVENTSSUPPORT ACTIVITIESLEE INITIATIVES, INC. SUPPORTS NONPROFIT HEALTH RELATED ORGANIZATIONS BY PROVIDING ANNUAL GRANTS BASED ON A COMMITTEE'S REVIEW OF GRANT APPLICATIONS FOR THE NEEDS OF THOSE ORGANIZATIONS THAT HAVE APPLIED FOR SUPPORT FOR VARIOUS HEALTH RELATED PROGRAMS.LEE INITIATIVES, INC. SUPPORTS INDIVIDUAL STUDENTS BY PROVIDING ANNUAL SCHOLARSHIPS BASED ON A COMMITTEE'S REVIEW OF SCHOLARSHIP APPLICATIONS FOR STUDENTS PURSING AN EDUCATION IN THE MEDICAL FIELD.THE SERVICE AREA OF THIS ORGANIZATION INCLUDES TWO (2) COUNTIES IN WESTERN PENNSYLVANIA.ADVOCACY ACTIVITIESLEE INITIATIVES, INC. PROVIDES AWARENESS OF THE NEEDS OF LOCAL NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS BY DISCUSSING THE MISSION OF THOSE ORGANIZATIONS AT FUNDRAISERS AND AN ANNUAL CEREMONY ANNOUNCING THE GRANTS THAT WERE AWARDED. THIS PROVIDES ADDITIONAL ADVERTISING FOR THESE ORGANIZATIONS WHICH HELPS TO INCREASE THEIR CONTRIBUTIONS BY THOSE IN ATTENDANCE OF THESE EVENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION ADOPTED FASB INTERPRETATION NO. 48 (FIN 48), ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, AS CODIFIED IN FASB ASC 740-10. THE CODIFIED INTERPRETATION REQUIRES THE ORGANIZATION TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN AND DETERMINE WHETHER IT IS MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT THAT THE TAX POSITION WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. THE ORGANIZATION HAS PERFORMED AN EVALUATION AND HAS DETERMINED THERE ARE NO MATERIAL UNRECOGNIZED TAX POSITIONS OR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT MEET THE REPORTING AND DISCLOSURE PROVISIONS OF FIN 48. THE ORGANIZATION RECORDS TAX PENALTIES AND INTEREST AS THEY OCCUR. FOR THE CURRENT YEAR ENDED, THE ORGANIZATION INCURRED NO TAX PENALTY OR INTEREST COSTS.
